.
.Ss2 Supported machines
.(bullet -offset indent
Sbus-based UltraSPARC systems (the Ultra 1, Ultra 1 Creator/Ultra1 Creator3D, 
Ultra 2/Ultra 2 Creator/Ultra 2 Creator 3D)
.It
PCI-based UltraSPARC systems (known to work on the Ultra 5, Ultra 10, Ultra 30
and Blade 100, Netra X1, and may work on many other systems)
.bullet)
.
.Ss2 Unsupported machines
.(bullet -offset indent
Chassis-based Enterprise Systems (Ex000, Ex500, E10000)
.bullet)
.Pp
The minimal configuration requires 32 MB of RAM and ~60 MB of disk space.
To install the entire system requires much more disk space, and to run
X or compile the system, more RAM is recommended, as
.Nx
with 32 MB of RAM feels like
.Tn Solaris
with 32 MB of RAM - slow.
Note that until you have at least 64 MB of RAM, getting more RAM is more
important than getting a faster CPU.
.
.Ss2 Supported devices
.(bullet -offset indent
Ethernet devices
.(bullet -compact
Sbus LANCE ethernet
.Pq Em le
.It
Sbus HME ethernet
.Pq Em hme
.It
Sbus BigMac ethernet
.Pq Em be
.It
PCI HME ethernet
.Pq Em hme
.It
PCI Tulip
.Pq Em tlp
.It
PCI ERI
.Pq Em gem
.bullet)
.It
Video devices
.(bullet -compact
Sbus cgsix
.bullet)
.It
SCSI host controllers
.(bullet -compact
ncr53c9x based controllers
.Pq Em esp
.It
ncr53c8xx based controllers
.Pq Em siop No or Em esiop
.It
ISP10x0 based controllers
.Pq Em isp
.It
Adaptec AHA-2x4x[U][2][W] cards and onboard PCI designs using the AIC-7770,
AIC-7850, AIC-7860, AIC-7870, AIC-7880 and AIC-789x chipsets.
.bullet)
.It
PCI IDE host controllers
.(bullet -compact
CMD Tech PCI064[3689] IDE Controllers
.Pq Em pciide
.(Note
Access to hard disks on the secondary PCIIDE channel currently do not work, but
CD-ROM does.
.Note)
.bullet)
.It
Serial devices
.(bullet -compact
Sbus z8530 serial
.Pq Em zs
.It
PCI 16550-based su and su-pnp serial
.Pq Em com
.bullet)
.It
Parallel devices
.(bullet -compact
Sbus parallel ports
.Pq Em bpp
.It
PCI/Ebus parallel ports
.Pq Em lpt
.bullet)
.Pp
There are a large number of untested PCI drivers that have never
been tested on UltraSPARC PCI systems that may
.Sq "just work" .
.
.Ss2 Unsupported devices
.(bullet -offset indent
Floppy drives
.It
Audio devices
.(bullet -compact
PCI based system audio
.Pq Em audiocs
.bullet)
.It
Serial devices
.(bullet -compact
PCI based systems
.Pq Em sab
.bullet)
.It
Video devices
.(bullet -compact
Creator3D framebuffers
.Pq Em ffb
.It
General PCI VGA support
.bullet)

